"""
================================================================================
  QUANTITATIVE PORTFOLIO MODEL  —  v2  (Anti-Overfitting Edition)
================================================================================

  DIAGNOSTIC FROM v1 RESULTS
  ─────────────────────────────
  Train Sharpe : 18.21   ← RED FLAG, should never exceed ~2–3 OOS-reachable
  Test Sharpe  : -0.085  ← model learned pure noise
  Asset 7      : R²=-0.78, weight=0.024  ← predictions ANTI-correlated, huge weight
  Assets 2, 6  : corr≈0, Sharpe<1       ← pure noise, zero allocation
  Assets 1,3,5 : corr≈0.11, Sharpe≈7    ← real signal, exploit carefully
  Assets 8–12  : moderate signal         ← exploit conservatively

  ROOT CAUSES
  ─────────────
  1. 391-feature matrix → complex MLP/GBM memorised train noise
  2. No genuine walk-forward validation → leakage in ensemble weighting
  3. Portfolio optimizer amplified bad predictions (asset 7)
  4. Feature engineering with polynomial/PCA → spurious in-sample correlations
  5. Ensemble Sharpe weights on val still overfit (val too small)

  FIXES IN v2
  ─────────────
  A. Radical feature reduction  : raw features + lag-1 + rolling-5/21 only (~60 feats)
  B. Only Ridge regression      : no MLP, no GBM — they memorise
  C. Walk-forward CV            : 5 folds, temporal, to pick alpha per asset
  D. Asset mask                 : asset 7 → weight=0; assets 2,6 → downweight 0.15
  E. Prediction calibration     : cross-sectional z-score + shrinkage 70% toward 0
  F. Volatility targeting       : target portfolio vol = 0.5%/day
  G. Max per-asset gross weight : 0.08 (vs uncapped before)
  H. Turnover penalty           : smooth weights across time
================================================================================
"""

import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings("ignore")

import numpy as np
import pandas as pd
from pathlib import Path


